#Text=Roger Dudley
#Text=Roger Dudley ( born between 1535 and 1545 – 1586 ?
#Text=/1588 ? ) was an English soldier .
#Text=Dudley was born in London , England , and may have been baptised in Yardley Hastings , Northamptonshire .
#Text=Dudley 's parentage has never been satisfactorily established .

#Text=Genealogist and researcher Marshall Kirk in 1993 published the results of his exhaustive survey of the Sutton Dudley families , and came to the conclusion that Roger was the son of Henry Sutton Dudley .
#Text=Roger may also be the Roger Dudley who was matriculated as pensioner at Christ Church College , Cambridge , in 1566 , but left without a degree .

#Text=It is believed that Roger married , on 8 June 1575 , at Lidlington , Bedfordshire , Susannah ( née Thorne ) , herself recorded as having been born on 5 March 1559/60 in Northamptonshire , and baptised at Yardley Hastings , the daughter of Thomas Thorne and Mary Purefoy , ( the Purefoys being of noble descent ) . [ 1 ]
#Text=He is reported to have been a Captain in the Earl of Leicester 's militia , fighting with a commission from Elizabeth I , and under the banner of Henry of Navarre .
#Text=He was thought to have died at the Battle of Ivry , France in 1590 .
#Text=However , the Reverend Cotton Mather of Boston wrote :
#Text=" Thomas Dudley 's father was Captain Roger Dudley , -- slain in the wars , when -- his son , and one only daughter were very young " .

#Text=The will of Thomas Dorne ( Thorne ) of Yardley Hastings , Gent . , dated 29 Oct 1588 , bequeathed " to the children of Susan Dudley , my Daughter , widow , £10 to be equally divided " . ( S1 , S11 ) .
#Text=Therefore , Roger was dead at the time of the will of his father-in-law , which , written in 1588 , eliminates the Battle of Ivry as a possible date for his death .

#Text=It is most probable that he died at the Siege of Zutphen in 1586 , having followed his kinsman , Robert Dudley , 1st Earl of Leicester , who was a principal figure in that battle , which also claimed the life of Leicester 's nephew Sir Philip Sidney .

#Text=Marshall K. Kirk suggests that Roger made his home after his father 's death with Peter Grey , a " Queen 's servant " , whose manor of Segenhoe was two miles from Lidlington , ( Bedfordshire ) , where Roger was later married .
#Text=Roger and Susannah Dudley raised at least five children , listed as :
#Text=Thomas Dudley ( second governor of Massachusetts Bay Colony )
#Text=Mary Dudley
#Text=Richard Dudley ( b. 1583 – d. 20 Aug 1603 )
#Text=Dorothy Dudley
#Text=David Dudley

#Text=Susannah is recorded as having died in 1585 during childbirth , at St. Dunstan 's , London and her name appears again three years later in a will , dated 29 October 1588 , ( Probate 9 May 1589 ) , in which Thomas Thorne bequeaths ... " to the Children of Susan Dudley , my Daughter ...
